column15: What is your annual household income?
column16: What was your overall impression of this event (quality, lighting, sound, value)?
column17: Please share any other suggestions or ideas that would help us enhance your experience at Gesa Power House Theatre. If you would like someone to respond to your feedback, please include your contact information. Thank you!

column16: Gina Chavez is amazing!! Thank you for bringing her here!!
column17: Places to dance when you bring a singer + band 😊

column16: Most excellent!!!! The best concert event I've been to at Gesa and I don't even speak or understand Spanish. I went to support a young lesbian LatinaX Artist and I was moved beyond words with this young lady and her bands performance!!!! Thank You Gesa House!!!! KatieD

column17: Please keep more top quality acts like gina chavez and less clown type acts. Thank you.
Have you thought about serving liquor as well? Would be a nice addition.

column16: Absolutely fantastic!! The one  main light that shines on the audience from the lighting above the stage was too intense it kind of made me want to put on my sunglasses but that is all . Just maybe turn down that bright light that shines on the audience. Gina was so much fun!!!👌❤️
What a fantastic show! I had a great time.

Excellent. Better than I expected. Gina and team were extremely talented. I was so energized by the show. The staff and volunteers were all happy and fun. It's contagious! Lighting was well done. A little loud so thanks for the ear plugs!
Perfection. A dynamic, high energy performance. Gave me good feels about her, us and our inclusive community. So grateful for the quality of programming and support for liberal arts in walla walla.
column17: Please keep doing what you’re doing. Spreading the word about upcoming events is key.

column16: Great evening of music, sound was good but stage lighting could have been better. Spot lighting and mood lights are a great way to enhance performances.

Gina Chavez obviously has some smooth and powerful pipes.  Despite that, I think some of the instruments that were captured on mic slightly overpowered her vocal delivery.  Great enthusiasm from both performers and audience made for a warm and delightful experience.  Hope they continue to return to the Gesa for future performances.  Thanks!

I have seen a lot of shows at GPHT and this was my favorite, mainly because of the high quality of the artists. Their show was high-energy, positive, and engaging. The theatre is always a great place to catch live music, with good lighting, sound, sight lines, and intimacy with the performers. Your staff always do an excellent job.
column17: I would appreciate having a divider panel installed between the two urinals in the men's restroom. Not everyone likes to pee with friends. Having a drinking fountain available would also be greatly appreciated.
